FBIS3-60763 "jptot001__l94011" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CHINA Tenth PRC Passenger Aircraft Hijacked to Taipei Taiwan Expected To Use `New Method' OW2812075193 Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News Network in Mandarin 0700 GMT 28 Dec 93 OW2812075193 Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News Network Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [From the "new" program] [Text] The 10th hijacked passenger plane belonging to a PRC airlines landed at Taoyuan Chiang Kai-shek (CKS) Airport at 1413 local time [0613 GMT] this afternoon. Airport police have learned the two hijackers are male and female. The male is named (Luo Chang-hu) and the female is known as (Wang I-yin). Claiming that they carried explosives, they demanded that Fuchien [Fujian] Airlines' (?Flight FC-518) bound from Chianghsi's [Jiangxi] Kanchou [Ganzhou] for Hsiamen [Xiamen] be diverted to Taiwan. There are 50 people on board, including eight crew members and 42 passengers. The plane was hijacked at 1312 local time. Our Air Force immediately learned of the hijacking. Because the Chinese communists' Yun-7 aircraft is similar to military aircraft, our Air Force adopted serious precautionary measures. At 1422 local time, four F-5E's took off from Taiwan to guide the hijacked plane to Taoyuan CKS International Airport. Government officials have gone to the airport to handle the matter. According to Prime Minister Lien Chan and instructions from the Mainland Affairs Council, it is expected the government will adopt a new method for handling the hijacked plane.
